03/10/2006

In its latest monitoring reports, the European Commission said Bulgaria and Romania have made enough progress to enter the EU as scheduled on January 1st, 2007. 
However, the two countries will still be under scrutiny and will have to report to the EU Council every six months concerning progress they have made.
***
Montenegro resumed talks on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. 
The talks had been broken off while the republic was part of the former state union of Serbia-Montenegro. 
Officials now say they hope to wrap up the process by the end of the year.
***
US Defence Secretary Donald Rumsfeld paid a visit to Montenegro, becoming the first senior US official to do so since the country gained independence. 
He voiced Washington's full support for Montenegro's bid to join NATO's Partnership for Peace programme. 
Rumsfeld then travelled to Tirana for an annual meeting of Southeast Europe defence ministers.
***
Serbia and Republika Srpska signed an agreement on special parallel relations. 
The agreement extends an existing deal signed in 2001. 
The Serbian leaders were accompanied by a 300-member business delegation, in a bid to boost economic ties.
***
Croatian Justice Minister Ana Lovrin met with Serbian counterpart Zoran Stojkovic in Zagreb. 
The two ministers said they would soon seal a new memorandum on bilateral co-operation related to processing war crimes cases. 
It would pave the way for the exchange of lists of suspects and evidence.
***
Greek Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis met with UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan and said her country would never allow Macedonia to join NATO or the EU until the name dispute with Greece is resolved. 
She also met with US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice to discuss the Kosovo issue.
***
Daniel Fried, US assistant secretary of state for European and Eurasian Affairs, paid a two-day visit to Kosovo for talks with international and local officials. 
He also met with Serb political leaders in the divided city of Mitrovica.
(Various sources – 26/09/06 – 03/10/06)
